Creative Automation SaaS (Placid.app Alternative)
Planning
 Research Placid.app features
Write implementation plan
 Get user approval
Phase 1 — Project Scaffold
 Initialize Next.js 14 project (App Router)
 Set up Prisma + PostgreSQL (via Supabase or local)
 Set up NextAuth.js for authentication
 Configure Stripe for billing
 Set up Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
Phase 2 — Core: Template Editor
 Canvas editor with Fabric.js (drag-and-drop)
 Layer panel (text, image, shape, background layers)
 Text layer: font, size, color, position
 Image layer: upload, URL, dynamic placeholder
 Shape layer: rectangles, circles
 Save/load template JSON to database
 Template library (grid view, create, duplicate, delete)
Phase 3 — Image Generation Engine
 Server-side rendering with Puppeteer (HTML → PNG/JPEG/PDF)
 REST API endpoint: POST /api/v1/images
 Accept template_id + dynamic variables
 Return image URL (stored in Cloudinary or S3)
 Rate limiting per plan
Phase 4 — User Dashboard
 Projects page (organize templates by project)
 API Keys management page
 Usage stats (API calls this month)
 Team members (optional)
Phase 5 — Auth & Billing
 Sign up / Sign in (email + Google OAuth)
 Pricing page (Free / Pro / Business tiers)
 Stripe checkout + webhooks
 Plan limits enforcement
Phase 6 — Landing Page
 Hero section
 Features section
 Pricing section
 CTA + footer
Verification
 Test template editor (create/save/load)
 Test API image generation
 Test auth flow
 Test Stripe billing flow
